        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><strong>Intelligence Community Authorities Clarification Act</strong></p> <p>This bill prohibits the elements of the intelligence community from conducting any intelligence-related activities that do not have a nexus to foreign intelligence or counterintelligence. The President may waive this prohibition for a period of up to one year if the President provides to Congress a written declaration that the waiver is important to U.S. national security interests.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
